I can only think of a few things here:

-Does the laptop you’re currently using have the NI FRC Game Tools installed? Based on your mention of the Driver Station, it sounds like yes (the DS is part of the Game Tools), but it’s worth mentioning just in case; the Game Tools is what installs the USB network driver for the roboRIO.

-I see this:

What we’ve tried:
Turning off WiFi on the PC
Disabling all other internet adapters

Which depending on the exact order that interacted with this:

The 1st setup:
RIO connected over Ethernet (directly to PC - we didn’t have a radio)

Did you try direct Ethernet before USB? If so, did you disable all other network adapters before plugging in the USB? The USB connection itself is recognized as a network adapter in Windows, so if you disabled that, USB won’t work either.
